  "title": "Installation & Commissioning Engineer",
  "description": "<p>Our client is a <strong>Marine and Offshore Industry.</strong> Due to business needs, they are now recruiting a <strong>Installation & Commissioning Engineer</strong> to be part of their Team for ongoing transformation projects. They are located in the <strong>West </strong>- easily accessible.<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Coordinate resources across internal teams and external partners to ensure projects progress smoothly and meet defined objectives.</li><li>Identify potential technical challenges or operational bottlenecks and develop practical solutions.</li><li>Work with management and clients to define project requirements, scope, and objectives that align with organizational goals.</li><li>Assign project tasks to appropriate stakeholders and monitor progress through regular status updates.</li><li>Analyze risks and opportunities, providing recommendations and escalating issues when necessary.</li><li>Serve as the primary point of contact between company teams and external resources, ensuring clear and timely communication.</li><li>Maintain accurate and comprehensive project documentation, including plans, reports, and progress records.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma in Electrical Engineering or related field of study.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in a related field.</li><li>Familiarity with risk management and quality assurance control.</li><li>Strong working knowledge of Microsoft Project and Microsoft Planner.</li></ul><p><br /><em>Interested candidates who wish to apply for the advertised position, please click </em><em><strong>APPLY NOW</strong></em><em> or email an updated copy of your resume/cv.</em></p><p><em>We regret that only shortlisted candidate will be notified.</em><br /></p><p><em>Email Address: </em><a href=\"mailto:jobs@recruitpedia.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><em>jobs@recruitpedia.sg</em></a></p><p><em>Recruitpedia Pte. Ltd.</em><br /><em>EA License No: 19C9682</em><br /><em>EA Personnel No: R25157233 (Loh Pooi Keng)</em></p>",
